ilmbase
------------------------------------------
General utility libraries used by OpenEXR:

* Half is a class that encapsulates our 16-bit floating-point format.
* IlmThread is a thread abstraction library for use with OpenEXR
and other software packages.  It currently supports pthreads and
Windows threads.
* Imath implements 2D and 3D vectors, 3x3 and 4x4 matrices, quaternions
and other useful 2D and 3D math functions.
* Iex is an exception-handling library.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2

Build requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.5-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gcc-g++-3.4.4-3
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.openexr.com/

Canonical download:
  http://savannah.nongnu.org/download/openexr/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ilmbase-1.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ilmbase-1.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ilmbase-1.0.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ilmbase-1.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libilmbase-devel-1.0.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libilmbase6-1.0.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

